50|$|On 9 September 2011, {{an army of}} Al-Shabaab fighters {{attacked}} the Somali town of Elwaq, resulting {{in the deaths of}} 12 soldiers. Within 8 hours, the <b>Islamists</b> army claimed they had full control of Elwaq and that the remaining Somali soldiers fled the town. The next day, Somali troops attempted to recapture the town from <b>Islamists</b> militians. After hours of fighting, the <b>Islamists</b> reportedly fled the town on technicals. Al-Shabaab claimed that they killed 70 Somali soldiers and that they captured 10 military vehicles. The bodies of 30 <b>Islamists</b> were later discovered by the army, the dead including 8 children.|$|R
